results.name: Number of strict knapsack factorizations of n.
comment: A strict knapsack factorization is a finite set of positive integers > 1 such that every subset has a different product.
example: Missing from this list are (2*6*12), (3*4*12), (2*3*4*6), which are not knapsack.
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Jan 04 2019
